FT  21 MAR 92 / International Company News: St Paul Cos may float part of
Nuveen unit
THE St Paul Companies, the US property/casualty insurer, yesterday said it
might make an initial public offering of a minority stake in Nuveen, writes
Karen Zagor in New York.
Chicago-based Nuveen is the oldest and largest investment banking and asset
management firm specialising in the underwriting, trading and marketing of
municipal bonds and tax-free investment products. Its assets under
management increased four-fold in the last five years while annual sales
doubled.
The St Paul Companies said yesterday if a decision is made to go ahead with
an offering, it will be announced in the next few weeks.
Minnesota-based St Paul Companies also owns Minet Holdings of the UK.
